<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-04T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115/20734: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-04T18:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 4,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 4—2:15
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>In Prize Court yesterday President dealt with claims arising from
                                reprisals order of March 11th, 1915, ordering those who appeared as
                                claimants to select three cases and plead within a period of 14
                                days, 7 days later Crown’s answer to be delivered, trial to follow
                                speedily to wind up outstanding business.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>